# Testing Patterns and Best Practices

## Test Structure
Tests are organized in [test/](mdc:test/) directory mirroring the lib structure.

## Test Organization

### 1. Test Directory Structure
```
test/
├── data/
│   ├── repositories/          # Repository tests
│   └── services/             # Service tests
├── domain/
│   └── models/               # Model tests
├── mocks/                    # Mock implementations
└── UI/                      # ViewModel tests
    ├── auth/
    ├── home/
    ├── profile/
    └── hike_details/
```

### 2. Mock Setup
Mocks are located in [test/mocks/](mdc:test/mocks/) and generated using build_runner.

## ViewModel Testing Patterns

### 1. Test Setup
```dart
setUp(() {
  mockProfileRepository = MockProfileRepository();
  mockUserRepository = MockUserRepository();
  
  viewModel = ProfilePageViewModel(
    profileRepository: mockProfileRepository,
    userRepository: mockUserRepository,
  );
});
```

### 2. Loading State Tests
```dart
test('should set loading state correctly during operation', () async {
  // Arrange
  expect(viewModel.isLoading, false);
  
  when(mockRepository.operation()).thenAnswer((_) async {
    expect(viewModel.isLoading, true); // Should be loading during operation
    return result;
  });
  
  // Act
  await viewModel.someAsyncOperation();
  
  // Assert
  expect(viewModel.isLoading, false); // Should be false after operation
});
```

### 3. Error Handling Tests
```dart
test('should handle errors gracefully', () async {
  // Arrange
  when(mockRepository.operation()).thenThrow(Exception('Error'));
  
  // Act & Assert
  await viewModel.someAsyncOperation(); // Should not throw
  
  // Verify loading state is reset
  expect(viewModel.isLoading, false);
  
  // Verify error handling
  verify(mockRepository.operation()).called(1);
});
```

### 4. Async Operation Tests
```dart
test('should handle async operations correctly', () async {
  // Arrange
  when(mockRepository.operation()).thenAnswer((_) async => result);
  
  // Act
  final result = await viewModel.someAsyncOperation();
  
  // Assert
  expect(result, equals(expectedResult));
  expect(viewModel.isLoading, false);
});
```

## Repository Testing Patterns

### 1. Repository Method Testing
```dart
test('should return hikes from repository', () async {
  // Arrange
  final expectedHikes = [Hike(id: 1, name: 'Test Hike')];
  when(mockBackendApi.getHikes()).thenAnswer((_) async => expectedHikes);
  
  // Act
  final result = await repository.getAllAvailableHikes();
  
  // Assert
  expect(result, equals(expectedHikes));
  verify(mockBackendApi.getHikes()).called(1);
});
```

### 2. Error Handling Tests
```dart
test('should handle API errors gracefully', () async {
  // Arrange
  when(mockBackendApi.getHikes()).thenThrow(Exception('API Error'));
  
  // Act & Assert
  expect(
    () => repository.getAllAvailableHikes(),
    throwsA(isA<Exception>()),
  );
});
```

## Mock Usage Patterns

### 1. Mock Repository Setup
```dart
class MockProfileRepository extends Mock implements ProfileRepository {}
class MockUserRepository extends Mock implements UserRepository {}
class MockHikeRepository extends Mock implements HikeRepository {}
```

### 2. Mock Behavior Setup
```dart
// Setup mock behavior
when(mockProfileRepository.getUserProfileById(any))
    .thenAnswer((_) async => Profile(firstName: 'Test'));

// Verify mock calls
verify(mockProfileRepository.getUserProfileById('user123')).called(1);
```

### 3. Mock Async Operations
```dart
// Async mock setup
when(mockRepository.asyncOperation())
    .thenAnswer((_) async {
      await Future.delayed(Duration(milliseconds: 100));
      return result;
    });

// Test async behavior
test('should handle async operations', () async {
  final result = await viewModel.operation();
  expect(result, isNotNull);
});
```

## Test Helper Functions

### 1. Common Test Data
```dart
// Create test profiles
Profile createTestProfile({String? firstName, String? lastName}) {
  return Profile(
    firstName: firstName ?? 'Test',
    lastName: lastName ?? 'User',
    email: 'test@example.com',
  );
}

// Create test hikes
Hike createTestHike({int? id, String? name}) {
  return Hike(
    id: id ?? 1,
    name: name ?? 'Test Hike',
    description: 'Test Description',
  );
}
```

### 2. Async Test Helpers
```dart
// Wait for async operations
Future<void> waitForAsync() async {
  await Future.delayed(Duration.zero);
}

// Pump widget for widget tests
Future<void> pumpWidget(WidgetTester tester) async {
  await tester.pump();
  await tester.pumpAndSettle();
}
```

## Testing Best Practices

### 1. Test Naming Convention
```dart
// Use descriptive test names
test('should load profile when user ID is valid', () async {});
test('should handle network errors gracefully', () async {});
test('should update loading state during operation', () async {});
```

### 2. Arrange-Act-Assert Pattern
```dart
test('should update profile successfully', () async {
  // Arrange
  final profile = createTestProfile();
  when(mockRepository.updateProfile(any)).thenAnswer((_) async {});
  
  // Act
  await viewModel.updateProfile(profile);
  
  // Assert
  expect(viewModel.profile, equals(profile));
  verify(mockRepository.updateProfile(profile)).called(1);
});
```

### 3. Test Isolation
```dart
setUp(() {
  // Fresh mocks for each test
  mockRepository = MockRepository();
  viewModel = ViewModel(repository: mockRepository);
});

tearDown(() {
  // Clean up after each test
  viewModel.dispose();
});
```

### 4. Async Test Handling
```dart
test('should handle async operations', () async {
  // Use async/await properly
  await viewModel.asyncOperation();
  
  // Verify state changes
  expect(viewModel.isLoading, false);
});
```

## Common Testing Anti-Patterns

### 1. Avoid Manual Delays
```dart
// ❌ Avoid
await Future.delayed(Duration(milliseconds: 100));

// ✅ Use proper async/await
await viewModel.operation();
```

### 2. Don't Test Implementation Details
```dart
// ❌ Avoid - Testing private methods
expect(viewModel._privateMethod(), isTrue);

// ✅ Test public behavior
expect(viewModel.publicProperty, isTrue);
```

### 3. Don't Forget Error Cases
```dart
// ❌ Avoid - Only testing happy path
test('should load data', () async {
  await viewModel.loadData();
  expect(viewModel.data, isNotNull);
});

// ✅ Test both success and error cases
test('should handle loading errors', () async {
  when(mockRepository.loadData()).thenThrow(Exception('Error'));
  await viewModel.loadData();
  expect(viewModel.errorMessage, isNotNull);
});
```

## Running Tests

### 1. Run All Tests
```bash
flutter test
```

### 2. Run Specific Test File
```bash
flutter test test/UI/home/home_view_model_test.dart
```

### 3. Run Tests with Coverage
```bash
flutter test --coverage
```

### 4. Generate Mock Files
```bash
flutter packages pub run build_runner build
```
